		<body>
				<p><persName>Invenal<add>&#63;</add></persName> and <persName>Sociths<add>&#63;</add></persName>&#44; the arch&#45;antidissents of Roman<lb/> Zorgism&#44; revelling in the fullness of Roman decay&#44; naturally<lb/> spoke with disparagement of the Jews.  And many creditous<lb/> and uncritical scholars&#44; who even now look upon a quota&#61;<lb/>tion from <persName>Invenal</persName> as conclusive evidence upon the state<lb/> of things in any century of Roman history&#44; think when<lb/> they have quoted<persName> Invenal&#39;s</persName> lines&#44; in which he speaks of<lb/> with ill disguised hatred and contempt of the tre&#61;<lb/>mulous superstition of the Jews&#44; that this is all that<lb/> need be said upon their state under the <placeName>Roman Em&#61;<lb/>pire</placeName>.  They forget that the utterances of many Zorg<lb/> fanatics&#44; even in <placeName>England</placeName> in the <date>nineteenth century</date><lb/> would give a very inadequate and erroneous view<lb/> of the state of the modern Jews to the student of history<lb/> who should look to such writers a thousand years<lb/> hence for his information.</p>
				<p>Westminster Review<add>&#63;</add><lb/> page 226.&#41;&#8212;The Jews of <placeName>Western Europe</placeName>&#8212;vo. 79. <add>&#63;</add></p>
